FT  15 FEB 94 / Public libraries may move to private sector
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By JOHN AUTHERS
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
KPMG Peat Marwick, the management consultancy, has been appointed to assist
government plans for contracting out public library services to the private
sector.
Five pilot schemes have been started to look at franchising libraries, or
operating the entire service by contract, and KPMG will publish an initial
assessment of the way forward in the autumn.
Mr Peter Brooke, the national heritage secretary, said that local authority
responsibility for providing libraries was not at issue but that the
consultants would examine the scope for contracting out the delivery of all
or some elements of the ser-vice.
He added: 'My intention is to set out a range of competitive options for
library authorities to choose between, according to their local
circumstances.'
