   BRUSSELS
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
The European Union said yesterday it had extended the duration of temporary
anti-dumping duties of 49.9 to 97 per cent on imports of Japanese television
cameras, AP reports from Brussels.
The customs duties would take effect on Saturday and last for two months.
The prolongation of levies - to allow the EU Commission to complete its
investigation of the Japanese imports - was announced in the EU's official
journal.
The EU defines dumping as selling goods abroad for prices lower than
production cost or prices charged in domestic markets.
