FT  15 FEB 94 / Romania faces general strike
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By VIRGINIA MARSH
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   BUCHAREST
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
Alfa Cartel, Romania's second largest trade union bloc, said yesterday it
was postponing a general strike scheduled for tomorrow until February 28 in
order to join forces with CNSLR-Fratia, the country's other main union
confederation, writes Virginia Marsh in Bucharest.
In addition to mounting industrial stoppages and pickets, the strikers plan
to block roads and fuel deliveries, interrupt telecommunications every 10
minutes and cut bread production by two-thirds, CNSLR-Fratia said.
The two unions, which together represent 4.8m workers, are demanding the
government accelerate economic reform, improve the social security system
and take measures to solve the 'financial blockage'.
In recent weeks, many workers have not been paid because of a liquidity
crisis at highly-indebted state concerns. Inter-enterprise debt has risen to
an all-time high of Dollars 2.8bn, according to the finance ministry.
