FT  14 FEB 94 / Arts: Today's Television
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER DUNKLEY
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
Why do we so readily talk about 'shoplifting' when we mean theft? People who
steal from shops are just as much thieves as the chaps in black masks with
sacks marked 'Swag'. Even the publicity for Cutting Edge uses the silly
euphemism. The programme looks at the efforts made by shops and police to
hold back the rising tide of shop theft, and interviews 'Megan' who is
described as 'Britain's top shoplifter', meaning Britain's worst shop thief
presumably (9.00 C4).
Horizon studies the way in which air crashes are investigated (9.00 BBC2).
Panorama reports on asthma, a subject on which we have had a fairly recent
programme (9.30 BBC1).
BBC2's Picasso Season continues with Richardson On Picasso which describes
the beginnings of cubist sculpture (10.00) and Picasso And The Dealers which
promises to locate all 23 bronze casts of 'Head Of A Woman' (10.20).
Olympic Grandstand will be showing all the greatest moments from Torvill and
Dean's Olympic career (11.15 BBC2).
