<HEADLINE>
FT  12 FEB 94 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The pepper market was more active this week as more buyers tried to cover
neglected positions, reports Man Producten. White pepper remained very
steady. Selling pressure was limited because of the Chinese year. Spot white
was quoted at USDollars 2,900 a tonne and nearby shipment at Dollars 2,750
cif. Black pepper prices continued to rise as reports from India indicated
that the new crop was even worse than expected. It remains to be seen
whether there will be much pepper left for export purposes because India's
consumption must be at least 30.000 tonnes and the crop may fall short by
some 40.000 tonnes. In response to the Indian situation other producers
increased their prices or withdrew completely. Spot black No. 1 was offered
at Dollars 1,600-Dollars 1,650 a tonne, with forward positiomns commanding
premiums.
